ring fence
Homonym Number:
Word Class: verb
Sense Number:
Definition:to fence off an area of land [originally used to form a boundary between neighbouring landowners.]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka ring-fence
